1. Pronašao je *zamku* u šumi. (*zamku* - noun, accusative case) (He found a trap in the forest.)
2. Molim te da mi pomogneš da izbjegnem *zamku*. (*zamku* - noun, accusative case) (Please help me avoid a trap.)
3. Lovci su postavili *zamke* za divlje životinje. (*zamke* - noun, plural, nominative case) (Hunters set traps for wild animals.)
4. Kada se susreo sa problemom, morao je pronaći *izlaz iz zamke*. (*zamke* - noun, genitive case) (When faced with a problem, he had to find a way out of the trap.)
5. Bio je *zamka* u koju je upao nesvjestan. (*zamka* - noun, nominative case) (It was a trap he fell into unaware.)
6. Zavukao se u *zamku* i nije znao kako da izađe. (*zamku* - noun, accusative case) (He got himself into a trap and didn't know how to get out.)
7. Ona je bila lukava i postavila mu *zamku*. (*zamku* - noun, accusative case) (She was cunning and set a trap for him.)
8. *Zamka* za miševe nije uspjela uhvatiti nijednog. (*zamka* - noun, nominative case) (The mousetrap failed to catch any.)
9. Pokušao je izbjeći *zamku* i uspio je. (*zamku* - noun, accusative case) (He tried to avoid a trap and succeeded.)
10. Postavio je *zamku* za ribu i čekao je satima. (*zamku* - noun, accusative case) (He set a trap for fish and waited for hours.)